{"id":"int-b6bc0aec","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-05T18:51:24.017459296Z","actor":"egyptiangio","issue_id":"teamarrv2-gye","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Shipped on dev: Jellyfin integration parallel to Emby. Refactored EmbyClient with PATH_PREFIX (Emby keeps /emby/, Jellyfin uses server root). Added schema columns, settings dataclass, read/update helpers, Pydantic models, /settings/jellyfin + /jellyfin/test routes, refresh hook in generation.py. Frontend: combined Emby and Jellyfin into a single 'Media Servers' tab. Visual verification via Playwright. 4 jellyfin client tests added (518 total pass)."}}
{"id":"int-760d23b8","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-05T23:12:11.981388112Z","actor":"egyptiangio","issue_id":"teamarrv2-71x","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Root cause: stale stream_match_cache rows had cached_event_data with home_team.name set but home_team.short_name=''. Diagnosed from user @millercentral's EPG XML (#201): {away_team_short} at {home_team_short} → '<display-name>at</display-name>', and {broadcast_feed_team} fell back to full team name on home feed ('Philadelphia Phillies Feed') because feed_team.short_name was empty. Fix: TeamMatcher._reconstruct_event now treats a row with name set but short_name empty as stale, returns None, deletes the cache row, and re-fetches via service.get_events on next match pass. Self-healing — no user action required. 4 tests added (522 total pass)."}}
{"id":"int-76057499","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-06T14:35:13.299227492Z","actor":"egyptiangio","issue_id":"teamarrv2-71x","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"open","old_value":"closed"}}
{"id":"int-15a299ff","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-06T18:08:31.789676702Z","actor":"egyptiangio","issue_id":"teamarrv2-71x","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Real fix on dev (3 layers): (1) refresh_event_status is now additive — overlays only mutable fields (status, scores, broadcasts, odds, fight_result_*) onto the original event. Teams and other static fields are preserved verbatim. ESPN's summary endpoint omits shortDisplayName, so the old code was wiping team.short_name=None over the populated scoreboard data on every refresh. (2) Service-layer backfill from team_cache: get_event/get_events/get_team_schedule walk teams and patch short_name/abbreviation/name from team_cache when missing. team_cache (refreshed on startup from /teams endpoints) is now the canonical identity source, decoupled from per-event endpoint shape. (3) ESPN _parse_team falls back to team.name (the short form, always populated) when shortDisplayName is missing — defense in depth for new endpoints. 17 new tests, 548 total pass."}}
